<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-03-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-03-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="397" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 822.00/369.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Consular Agent <persName type="from">Hedian</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Esmeraldas</hi>
                                </placeName> [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content" calendar="gregorian" when="1914-03-05"><hi rend="italic">Undated</hi></date><hi rend="italic">; Received March 5,
                                    1914</hi>].</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Government, after ineffectual attacks Tuesday and last night, retired.
                            Only one gunboat remains in sight.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hedian</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>